# Error Resolution Logging

## When to Log
- Build failures (Angular CLI, TypeScript compilation, Docker build)
- Runtime errors (API crashes, unhandled exceptions, database errors)
- API/integration errors (Twilio, SendGrid, QuickBooks, Stripe failures)
- Database errors (migration failures, RLS violations, connection issues)
- Deployment errors (ECS, CloudFront, RDS configuration)
- Offline sync errors (IndexedDB, Service Worker, deduplication)
- WebSocket errors (connection drops, auth failures)
- Any issue that takes >5 minutes to diagnose

## When NOT to Log
- Simple typos caught by linter
- ESLint/Prettier formatting warnings
- Expected test failures during TDD red phase
- Known issues already documented

## Category Prefixes
- `DB` — PostgreSQL, migrations, RLS, PgBouncer
- `AUTH` — JWT, refresh tokens, SSO, MFA
- `SYNC` — Offline sync, IndexedDB, Service Worker
- `SMS` — Twilio SMS/IVR
- `WS` — WebSocket/Socket.io
- `QB` — QuickBooks integration
- `NOTIF` — Email/push notifications, SQS
- `UI` — Angular components, NgRx, responsive
- `DEPLOY` — Docker, ECS, AWS infrastructure
- `PERF` — Performance, scaling, connection pools
- `SEC` — Security, multi-tenant isolation, encryption

## Log Location
`docs/ERROR_FIX_LOG.md`

## Format
```
### [CATEGORY-NNN] Error Title
**Date:** YYYY-MM-DD
**Error:** What happened
**Context:** What was being done
**Root Cause:** Why it happened
**Fix:** What was changed
**Prevention:** How to avoid this in the future
```
